# Everything here executes on Linux (Docker images, EC2, CI runners) — and this
# repo is commonly checked out on Windows, where git rewrites text files to CRLF.
# A shell script with CRLF fails immediately and cryptically on Linux:
#   bench/chaos.sh: line 14: set: pipefail: invalid option name
# (bash reads the trailing \r as part of the option). Docker/compose configs and
# the Maven wrapper have the same exposure.
#
# Committed blobs happen to be LF today only because core.autocrlf normalises on
# commit — an implicit guard that one differently-configured clone would remove.
# These rules make it explicit and independent of anyone's local git config, and
# keep the Windows working tree runnable under WSL.

*.sh        text eol=lf
mvnw        text eol=lf
Dockerfile  text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf
*.conf      text eol=lf
